PART 5: CROSSOVER ANALYSIS — WHEN DOES INTERVAL BEAT PALEY?
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

     p             H(Paley)          H(Interval)       Δ/H(P)   Winner
     7                  189                  175    +0.074074    PALEY
    11                95095                93027    +0.021747    PALEY
    19        1172695746915        1184212824763    -0.009821 INTERVAL

  Paley advantage decreasing: 7.41% → 2.17% → -0.98%
  The crossover prime p₀ is between 11 and 19.
  The only p ≡ 3 mod 4 in (11, 19) is p = 15 (not prime).
  So p₀ = 19 is the FIRST prime where interval beats Paley.

