    Paley connection set: [1, 3, 4, 5, 9]
    Step sizes: [1, 3, 4, 5, 9]
    Paley gaps between consecutive steps: [2, 1, 1, 4]
    Interval has NO gaps (steps 1,2,...,5)

===========================================================================
PART 7: PERMANENT INTERPRETATION
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
  H(T) = Σ_σ Π_{i=0}^{n-2} A[σ(i), σ(i+1)]
  This is a 'path permanent' — sum over Hamiltonian paths, not matchings.

  Van der Waerden analogue:
  For doubly stochastic matrices: perm(J/n) ≤ perm(M) is FALSE
  (VdW says perm(J/n) ≤ perm(M) — wait, VdW says MINIMUM is at J/n)
  So the flat matrix MINIMIZES the permanent.

  For H on tournaments:
  At small p: flat spectrum (Paley) MAXIMIZES H
  At large p: concentrated spectrum (interval) MAXIMIZES H
  The crossover suggests H is NOT Schur-concave in general.
  This is consistent with THM-134 (Schur-concavity fails at p≡1(4)).

DONE.
